He was admitted to Kemnay in 1650, and continued there till 1653, when in October he was deprived for deserting his charge, it being stated that he had a church not far from London.

It is said <Maidment's catalogue. p. 121) that he “was one of the Chaplains to King Charles 11. and also of the army that went into England ”.
